camera winds ]

3
00:01:08,468 --> 00:01:09,958
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

4
00:01:24,484 --> 00:01:26,475
[ Clicking, rustling ]

5
00:02:01,621 --> 00:02:02,610
[ Gasps ]

6
00:02:08,528 --> 00:02:10,393
[ Roaring ]

7
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:02,104
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

8
00:03:15,428 --> 00:03:18,591
[ Music swells ]

9
00:06:18,745 --> 00:06:21,942
[ Door opens, closes ]

10
00:06:22,014 --> 00:06:24,107
Marvin, you gotta come
see this shit.

11
00:06:24,183 --> 00:06:27,619
-Did you get my pictures?
-Yeah. You gotta come outside.

12
00:06:27,687 --> 00:06:29,552
Me and Des
found something.

13
00:06:31,124 --> 00:06:33,024
-What is it?
-You'll see.

14
00:06:35,728 --> 00:06:37,923
Mom's home.
She won't want me to leave.

15
00:06:37,997 --> 00:06:39,259
We can sneak past.

16
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:41,823
''Citizen's Arrest'' is on.
You gotta.

17
00:06:43,002 --> 00:06:44,731
What is it you want me to see?

18
00:06:46,873 --> 00:06:48,670
l think we found a dead body.

19
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:53,142
[ Chuckles ]

20
00:06:56,549 --> 00:06:59,017
Going out, mom.
Back in a few.

21
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,575
Stay close.

22
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,481
Marvin?

23
00:07:34,020 --> 00:07:36,113
Oh, shit,
it's too dark to see now,

24
00:07:36,189 --> 00:07:38,248
but the body's down there.

25
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:41,285
l don't see anything.

26
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,453
lt's at the bottom.

27
00:07:43,529 --> 00:07:44,621
You high, Rosy?

28
00:07:44,697 --> 00:07:45,857
No.

29
00:07:47,099 --> 00:07:49,192
lt's been, like, two hours.

30
00:07:52,705 --> 00:07:53,694
Jesus.

31
00:07:53,773 --> 00:07:55,400
Do you think it's real?

32
00:08:14,393 --> 00:08:15,860
When did you guys find it?

33
00:08:15,928 --> 00:08:17,418
Find what?

34
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,021
The body in the sewer.

35
00:08:19,098 --> 00:08:22,465
l don't know.
We were pretty messed up.

36
00:08:22,535 --> 00:08:24,093
Get doubles of these.

37
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:27,105
l want to send one to the cops.

38
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,903
lf l'd known you
were gonna get worked up,

39
00:08:29,976 --> 00:08:31,500
l wouldn't have shown you.

40
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,674
Did you finish
my biology homework?

41
00:08:39,252 --> 00:08:41,413
Look underneath.

42
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:56,391
What do you see?

43
00:08:56,469 --> 00:08:57,834
Garbageman.

44
00:08:57,904 --> 00:08:59,428
He's new.

45
00:09:06,312 --> 00:09:07,279
Garbageman.

46
00:09:07,346 --> 00:09:10,440
The dark guy
with the trash bags?

47
00:09:10,516 --> 00:09:12,950
He moved in last week
above Birdman.

48
00:09:23,696 --> 00:09:26,221
What are you looking at now?

49
00:09:26,299 --> 00:09:28,267
Um...

50
00:09:30,202 --> 00:09:31,362
Ma Bell.

51
00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:33,735
Still yammering
at the grandkids?

52
00:09:33,806 --> 00:09:34,966
Looks it.

53
00:09:36,175 --> 00:09:38,643
Did l tell you
l met your veiled lady?

54
00:09:43,816 --> 00:09:45,113
What's her name?

55
00:09:45,184 --> 00:09:48,483
Carmen.
She's a dentist's assistant.

56
00:09:53,859 --> 00:09:55,759
ls she nice?

57
00:09:55,828 --> 00:09:58,763
ls she nice?
Sure.

58
00:09:58,831 --> 00:10:00,662
l'll bring her around sometime.

59
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:01,961
You might like her.

60
00:10:03,703 --> 00:10:06,672
You might even,
l don't know, not die a virgin.

61
00:10:06,739 --> 00:10:07,865
Rosy...

62
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,567
Unless you're allergic
to that, too.

63
00:10:09,642 --> 00:10:11,439
Shut up.

64
00:10:11,510 --> 00:10:13,478
Well, don't be
so hypersensitive.

65
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:15,878
Oh, that gets funnier
each night.

66
00:10:17,917 --> 00:10:19,350
Oh, my God.

67
00:10:19,418 --> 00:10:22,615
World's Number-One Dad
just lost his shit.

68
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:25,822
And look.

69
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:30,862
l found that downstairs.

70
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:33,990
ls that Number-One Son?

71
00:10:34,066 --> 00:10:35,294
Yeah, and...

72
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:38,167
And l took this two days ago.

73
00:10:38,237 --> 00:10:39,636
You see the shadow?
lt moved.

74
00:10:39,705 --> 00:10:42,173
Oh, my God.
That shadow moved?

75
00:10:42,241 --> 00:10:43,173
Mm-hmm.

76
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:45,142
Well, call the National Guard.

77
00:10:45,211 --> 00:10:48,510
Call the Space Marines.
Call the cops.

78
00:10:48,581 --> 00:10:51,448
They love this great
fake-detective routine.

79
00:10:58,624 --> 00:11:00,114
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

80
00:11:47,406 --> 00:11:49,874
You're scaring yourself
because you're bored.

81
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:51,739
l'm only looking.

82
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:54,974
That picture is so blurry,
it could be Bigfoot.

83
00:11:55,981 --> 00:11:57,972
[ Door opens, closes ]

84
00:12:16,902 --> 00:12:19,234
[ Camera shutter clicks,
camera winds ]

85
00:12:42,928 --> 00:12:44,361
[ Gasps ]

86
00:13:52,231 --> 00:13:53,892
Hey, Rose.

87
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:56,025
Hey, Des.

88
00:13:56,101 --> 00:13:57,500
Check this out.

89
00:13:58,737 --> 00:14:00,671
Huh?
You got any matches?

90
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:05,739
What's up?

91
00:14:19,925 --> 00:14:20,949
[ Knock on door ]

92
00:14:21,026 --> 00:14:23,256
-[ Door opens ]
-Dinnertime!

93
00:14:23,329 --> 00:14:24,523
[ Door closes ]

94
00:14:24,597 --> 00:14:27,259
[ Camera shutter clicks,
camera winds ]

95
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:29,733
lf you can stand
to be away from the window

96
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:31,531
long enough to eat.

97
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:38,132
Hi, Ma.

98
00:14:40,512 --> 00:14:43,242
[ Sighs ]

99
00:14:43,315 --> 00:14:45,215
Oh, God.

100
00:14:46,318 --> 00:14:49,776
What the neighbors must think.

101
00:14:49,855 --> 00:14:51,914
[ Scoffs ]

102
00:14:51,991 --> 00:14:54,482
Hey, why do you
leave the lights on?

103
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,652
So they can see you?

104
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:56,660
Hey, Ma...

105
00:14:56,729 --> 00:15:01,257
l seen Rosy with this guy,
and, um...

106
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:03,324
and l think
he's a drug dealer.

107
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:07,030
Rosy's a big girl.

108
00:15:07,106 --> 00:15:10,667
Yeah, but don't you think lately
she's been acting kinda off?

109
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:14,144
[ Sighs ]

110
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:16,977
You didn't like the lunch
l made you.

111
00:15:19,018 --> 00:15:20,918
l took the pills.

112
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:27,056
You can't live on pills alone.

113
00:15:27,126 --> 00:15:30,118
Oh, baby.
You're so fragile.

114
00:15:30,195 --> 00:15:32,390
You can't afford to skip a meal.

115
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:34,523
Yeah, l wasn't hungry.

116
00:15:37,369 --> 00:15:42,363
l don't want to be made
to worry about you like this.

117
00:15:43,676 --> 00:15:48,136
Well, l been thinking again
about finding my own place.

118
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,479
You know that's not possible.

119
00:15:57,556 --> 00:15:59,990
Dr. Carson seems to think
it's a good idea.

120
00:16:00,059 --> 00:16:03,028
He sees you once a month.
He doesn't know how you are.

121
00:16:03,095 --> 00:16:06,030
l'm 2 4 years old, Ma.

122
00:16:06,098 --> 00:16:08,123
l'll take care of things.

123
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:14,799
Will you finish
your dinner tonight?

124
00:16:14,873 --> 00:16:16,898
l can't stay here forever.

125
00:16:19,912 --> 00:16:21,277
l love you.

126
00:16:26,418 --> 00:16:28,147
[ Door opens, closes ]

127
00:17:03,789 --> 00:17:06,314
[ Camera shutter clicks,
camera winds ]

128
00:17:32,718 --> 00:17:33,650
Carmen.

129
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,448
Hi.

130
00:17:35,521 --> 00:17:36,453
[ Laughs ]

131
00:17:36,522 --> 00:17:38,922
Uh, Carmen,
this is my brother.

132
00:17:38,991 --> 00:17:41,118
Marvin obviously knows
who you are.

133
00:17:41,193 --> 00:17:43,684
[ Chuckles ]

134
00:17:43,762 --> 00:17:46,526
Oh, my God.
You weren't kidding.

135
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,560
lt's kinda pervy.

136
00:17:54,907 --> 00:17:56,670
You got a good eye.

137
00:17:56,742 --> 00:17:59,176
l got good subjects.

138
00:17:59,244 --> 00:18:01,508
What he's got is a compulsion.

139
00:18:01,580 --> 00:18:03,775
How long
have you been doing this?

140
00:18:03,849 --> 00:18:05,146
1 0 years, l guess.

141
00:18:05,217 --> 00:18:07,082
Yeah, since he got sick.

142
00:18:07,152 --> 00:18:09,916
l was one of the last kids
to get Stricklers'.

143
00:18:11,256 --> 00:18:13,087
You were one of those
roach kids?

144
00:18:13,158 --> 00:18:16,286
Well, l prefer ''Bubble Boy.''

145
00:18:16,361 --> 00:18:17,919
Oh. Right on.

146
00:18:17,996 --> 00:18:19,224
What were they called?

147
00:18:19,298 --> 00:18:21,095
-Judas Breed.
-Right.

148
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:22,599
You ever see any of them?

149
00:18:22,668 --> 00:18:23,930
lt didn't work like that.

150
00:18:24,002 --> 00:18:26,869
[ Laughs ] Sure he did.
All the time.

151
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,406
Shut up, Rosy.

152
00:18:28,474 --> 00:18:31,204
He was on the phone
to the CDC every week.

153
00:18:31,276 --> 00:18:34,245
He thought he was Smokey
the Bear of giant roaches.

154
00:18:34,313 --> 00:18:36,213
[ Chuckles ]
l was 8 years old.

155
00:18:36,281 --> 00:18:38,215
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, try 1 6.

156
00:18:38,283 --> 00:18:40,274
His therapist said he felt bad

157
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,445
'cause they created the Judas
for kids like him.

158
00:18:42,521 --> 00:18:44,853
Kill the roaches
that are making them sick.

159
00:18:44,923 --> 00:18:47,824
You didn't tell me
l was on here!

160
00:18:47,893 --> 00:18:49,622
-Yeah, um...
-[ Laughs ]

161
00:18:49,695 --> 00:18:51,754
Did you want them back?

162
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:53,491
l mean, do you want them?

163
00:18:53,565 --> 00:18:56,864
No. l mean, why would l want
pictures of myself?

164
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,301
Can l have this one, though?

165
00:19:06,445 --> 00:19:08,037
Yeah, sure.

166
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:13,782
[ Thunder rumbles ]

167
00:19:20,459 --> 00:19:22,256
-May l look?
-Yeah, just a sec.

168
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:23,385
What do you see?

169
00:19:23,462 --> 00:19:25,054
Des is dealing Ma Bell dope.

170
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:26,563
What's a ''Des''?

171
00:19:26,632 --> 00:19:28,566
Desmond, her boyfriend.

172
00:19:28,634 --> 00:19:30,431
He's not my boyfriend.

173
00:19:32,237 --> 00:19:33,602
You okay?

174
00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:34,604
And Ma Bell.

175
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:37,836
She's always talking to her
grandkids, so we call her that.

176
00:19:37,910 --> 00:19:40,435
-Mrs. Leibowitz?
-Uh-huh. You know her?

177
00:19:40,512 --> 00:19:43,811
l hear her at night.
She's a phone-sex operator.

178
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:47,516
Are you okay?

179
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:49,850
Um...

180
00:19:49,922 --> 00:19:51,184
you smoke.

181
00:19:51,256 --> 00:19:52,587
What?

182
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:53,920
lt's an allergy thing.

183
00:19:53,992 --> 00:19:55,960
l put it out
before l came inside.

184
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,859
He's hypersensitive.

185
00:19:57,930 --> 00:20:00,626
Well, should l go?
l mean, l'm sorry, you know?

186
00:20:00,699 --> 00:20:02,792
-Sorry. lt's, uh...
-l'm sorry.

187
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:05,132
-l didn't think.
-lt's all right.

188
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:06,796
Yeah, take it easy.

189
00:20:15,781 --> 00:20:18,272
l think she likes you.

190
00:20:21,486 --> 00:20:23,147
[ Car alarm beeping ]

191
00:20:25,023 --> 00:20:27,014
[ Dog barking in distance ]

192
00:20:30,429 --> 00:20:31,862
[ Car alarm chirps ]

193
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:33,921
[ Thunder rumbles ]

194
00:20:38,737 --> 00:20:40,432
[ Metal clatters ]

195
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:04,854
Ma Bell's running
from something.

196
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:06,090
No kidding.

197
00:21:13,705 --> 00:21:15,036
[ Clicking ]

198
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:20,337
Garbageman's down there.

199
00:21:23,148 --> 00:21:25,309
Can you get me more film?

200
00:21:25,384 --> 00:21:27,113
l'm busy.

201
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,726
Aah !

202
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,876
Holy shit!

203
00:21:57,916 --> 00:21:59,144
What?

204
00:21:59,217 --> 00:22:01,208
He's hurt.

205
00:22:01,286 --> 00:22:02,548
l think there's blood.

206
00:22:02,621 --> 00:22:03,986
Where is he?

207
00:22:17,803 --> 00:22:19,737
[ Squishing ]

208
00:22:21,106 --> 00:22:23,040
-Where?
-He's right there.

209
00:22:23,108 --> 00:22:24,769
Shit!

210
00:22:33,285 --> 00:22:35,219
[ Shouting ]

211
00:22:43,995 --> 00:22:45,986
Jesus, what happened?

212
00:22:46,064 --> 00:22:47,656
l don't know.

213
00:22:49,668 --> 00:22:51,602
Well, what did you see?

214
00:22:55,807 --> 00:22:57,434
[ Thunder crashes ]

215
00:23:07,819 --> 00:23:09,810
[ Thud, scraping ]

216
00:23:21,867 --> 00:23:23,164
Mom?

217
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,896
Hmm?

218
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:25,902
Mom !

219
00:23:25,971 --> 00:23:26,903
Huh?

220
00:23:26,972 --> 00:23:28,872
We have to call the cops.

221
00:23:30,008 --> 00:23:31,999
[ Knock on door ]

222
00:23:34,613 --> 00:23:36,410
-Hi.
-Detective Dumars.

223
00:23:36,481 --> 00:23:39,006
Well, thanks for coming.

224
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:40,176
No problem.

225
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:42,516
Simone.

226
00:23:43,722 --> 00:23:46,020
[ Chuckles ]

227
00:23:46,091 --> 00:23:47,752
Do l know you?

228
00:23:49,895 --> 00:23:52,125
Do you want to come in?

229
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:53,323
Yeah.

230
00:23:53,398 --> 00:23:55,195
[ Sighs ]

231
00:23:57,803 --> 00:23:59,395
What seems to be the problem?

232
00:23:59,471 --> 00:24:01,268
Well...

233
00:24:01,339 --> 00:24:03,671
my kids think
they saw something.

234
00:24:03,742 --> 00:24:05,801
-Somebody was hurt.
-Killed.

235
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:10,978
[ Chuckles nervously ]

236
00:24:19,057 --> 00:24:22,959
Oh, um, my son is
a Stricklers' disease survivor.

237
00:24:23,028 --> 00:24:26,259
He's environmentally
hypersensitive.

238
00:24:26,331 --> 00:24:27,992
Oh. Must be very hard
on you.

239
00:24:28,066 --> 00:24:31,797
Yeah, it happened over there,
near the entrance of the alley.

240
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:33,360
His name's Desmond.

241
00:24:33,438 --> 00:24:34,996
Mm-hmm.

242
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:39,638
He was covered in blood,
and then he disappeared.

243
00:24:41,112 --> 00:24:43,307
He was hurt?

244
00:24:43,381 --> 00:24:44,541
Yeah.

245
00:24:48,119 --> 00:24:50,644
Was, uh...

246
00:24:50,722 --> 00:24:52,155
anybody else around?

247
00:24:52,224 --> 00:24:53,851
He saw the Garbageman.

248
00:24:53,925 --> 00:24:55,586
l think l did.

249
00:24:57,128 --> 00:24:59,722
Okay.
Okay, l bite.

250
00:24:59,798 --> 00:25:01,527
Who's the Garbageman?

251
00:25:06,104 --> 00:25:07,401
Him.

252
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,773
You took these pictures?

253
00:25:09,841 --> 00:25:12,105
-lt's his hobby.
-Yeah.

254
00:25:12,177 --> 00:25:13,974
l'm not sure it's legal.

255
00:25:14,045 --> 00:25:15,410
Oh...
[ Chuckles ]

256
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:17,243
He's harmless.

257
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:26,222
This guy was at the scene
when -- what's his name?

258
00:25:26,291 --> 00:25:28,589
-Desmond.
-When Desmond disappeared?

259
00:25:28,660 --> 00:25:31,060
Yeah, and there was blood.

260
00:25:31,129 --> 00:25:32,858
The rain washed it away.

261
00:25:32,931 --> 00:25:35,923
Get any pictures of that?

262
00:25:36,001 --> 00:25:37,866
No, l was out of film.

263
00:25:37,936 --> 00:25:39,233
Yeah, well...

264
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,904
Gee, l wonder what Desmond
does for a living.

265
00:25:45,977 --> 00:25:47,569
[ Rosy mumbles ]

266
00:25:47,646 --> 00:25:48,908
Rosy!

267
00:25:55,787 --> 00:25:57,448
Well, l, um...

268
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:02,326
might as well go have a chat
with the Garbageman.

269
00:26:13,438 --> 00:26:15,099
l don't see him.

270
00:26:31,156 --> 00:26:32,885
[ Sighs ]
The guy's harmless.

271
00:26:32,958 --> 00:26:34,186
ROS Y:
Well, who is he?

272
00:26:34,259 --> 00:26:36,250
He didn't see anything happen.

273
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:38,296
-Did you get his name?
-Never mind his name.

